title: Webauthn/FIDO2 2FA key support for Firefox Accounts
content:
Hi, Firefox Accounts (Fxa) support TOPT (Google authenticator etc) 2FA, which is pretty good, however it would be great if you could support Webauthn/FIDO2 (Yubikey etc).

There was a Bugzilla bug for this, https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1464888 opened 4 years ago, however about a year ago it was closed wontfix because it "is not currently on our roadmap"

Which seems like a really bad idea? Given that most security people, browsers and OSs are saying "passwordless is the future", and FIDO2 is how that will happen. And even passwordless aside, FIDO2 is a more robust and generally easier to use option than even TOTP apps

title: 1GB de RAM en consumo por Firefox y ralentizando el propio navegador y el PC
content: Desde las versiones 90+ de Firefox la opción de multiproceso, la cual solo pongo a 1 o 2 desapareció de la configuración. Al entrar en modo seguro aparecen las opciones, las cuales cambié pero no solucionó el problema y aún en este modo presentaba lentitud y uso excesivo de memoria entre 400 a 600 MB y mínimo 5 procesos. Deshabilite la aceleración por hardware y se mantuvo el problema. Al consultar los procesos de Firefox desde las herramientas propias del Navegador se aprecia uso excesivo de GPU entre 300 a 500 MB y procesos asociados a esta y red entre otros de las pestañas. Al comparar con el Administrador de tareas de windows con todas las aplicaciones del PC cerradas, este mostraba casi el doble de la sumas de los procesos que muestra firefox, 1200 MB aproximadamente y al menos 10 a 15 procesos, sin pestañas abiertas (solo la pestaña de marcadores) y con los complementos deshabilitados. Mi PC Tiene Windows 10, 6GB de RAM y Procesador Intel Core i3 m370. ¿Cómo se puede solucionar esto? Soy desarrollador web y esto me complica el Trabajo por la lentitud general del navegador y además me ralentiza el PC donde debo usar Herramientas de desarrollo. Gracias de antemano.

I will call HP tomorrow in their office hours and give them a hard time.

title: How to create a toggle to change this setting: Start searching for text when you start typing
content:
I regularly switch between two Firefox settings:

Search for text when you start typing: checked Search for text when you start typing: unchecked

I use a third-party scripting tool (Macro Express Pro) to automate the process so that a single hotkey toggles between the two settings. My macro looks something like this:

Text Type (Simulate Keystrokes): <F10> // Move focus to the Menu bar Delay: 800 milliseconds Text Type (Simulate Keystrokes): t // Tools Delay: 200 milliseconds Text Type (Simulate Keystrokes): s // Settings

Delay: 1000 milliseconds

Text Type (Simulate Keystrokes): <SHIFT><ALT>x // Toggle the search setting Delay: 50 milliseconds

Text Type (Simulate Keystrokes): <CONTROL><F4> // Close the setting pane

My macro is a bit unreliable. It works about 80% of the time. I could improve reliability a little by using longer delays, but my preference would be to do this in a more programmatic way, or at minimum, in a more direct way with fewer steps.

Is there a way to toggle this setting, for example, via about:config or by typing something in the address bar? The Firefox hotkey in the Settings pane is SHIFT + ALT + x. Is there a way to force this hotkey to be recognized in a regular Firefox window?

title: Password outdated
content: Hello, I tried to sign in to my firefox account on a new computer and it appears the rules for password format have changed such that my existing password is too short to be used. How should I proceed to either sign in or reset my password without affecting my existing firefox browsers and lockwise app? Thank you.
creator: john.lee3
